==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Somnambulation
<hw>Som*nam`bu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>somnus</ets> sleep + <ets>ambulatio</ets> a walking about, from
<ets>ambulare</ets> to walk. See <er>Somnolent</er>,
<er>Amble</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of walking in sleep, called also
<altname>sleepwalking</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somnambulator</ent>⟦br⟧
